 and cry about it and try to KS someone else's.  Though I agree that once in the rotation you should abide by the rotation guidelines, it's the most fair and straightforward way to do it without stepping on someone's toes imo.  Now granted, trying to get enough peeps together who are capable of taking out VS before someone on the rotation does will be quite the feat.  However, once on the rotation then not only have you secured a spot there but you will be able to then post the pick-ups spot on the rotation on the boards here and have enough signed up beforehand.  Sounds like a good plan at least in theory to me.  I'd much prefer going on a pick up raid in hopes of getting some ultra rare epic piece than have to buy it off someone for the ungodly amount of 50k just because they can take out the mob and want to sell it to procure guild funds.  Sorry but that just makes me sick.  I never have more than about 1k in the bank because I spend my time playing the game instead of sittin in Ebay commons trying to sell the caster cloak I rolled on because I felt I needed the money more than the caster needed the cloak.  I'm sure if I sold all the stuff I've acquired over the course of this game I'd have well over at least 30k in the bank right now.  However, I'm one of those goofy types that give away stuff to peeps who can use it.  But anyway, that's a whole nother can of worms there heh.  I say if you can do it mano then go for it!  Not everyone's so self centered that they're willing to leave the guild they love just so that they can be &quot;uber&quot; and automatically be in the &quot;rotation&quot; by default :P  Just my leetle 2 cp <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
